"Vietnamese People's Daily Network - Vietnamese Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng attends the third national digital technology enterprise development forum in Vietnam." 
"Two main conferences were held during the third national digital technology enterprise development forum in Vietnam, with discussions centered around the topics of digital technology enterprises and the country's digital transformation, as well as the economic recovery and development after the COVID-19 pandemic." 
"Minister of Information and Communications Nguyen Meng Xiong stated that despite the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, the number and business revenue of Vietnamese digital technology enterprises still showed growth trends in 2021, reaching nearly 10%." 
"In 2021, a large number of typical digital products were cultivated in Vietnam, focusing on solving the major problems facing the country. Many digital products have gone abroad and the ranking of Vietnamese digital technology has been improved." 
"Minister Nguyen Meng Xiong calls on digital technology enterprises to take on the responsibility of developing the country's digital transformation platform, as developing these digital platforms is equivalent to fulfilling the country's mission.
At the forum, leaders from various departments and national agencies, as well as enterprises, organizations, and individuals involved in researching, developing, applying, and transferring digital technology, shared their ideas and solutions on how to mobilize and gather resources from society to develop Vietnamese technology enterprises and promote the national digital transformation.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized in his speech at the forum that digital transformation is the only path for the world and an objective requirement for development.
Digital transformation has become a global issue and serves the entire population, therefore it is necessary to mobilize the participation of all citizens.
The people and enterprises are the core, main body, goal, and driving force of digital transformation.
Therefore, all policies should be for the people and enterprises.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng emphasized that the digital transformation must reflect the national spirit, and must be driven by internal factors, such as strategy, long-term and decisive factors, while external factors are important and breakthrough points.
He also believes that digital transformation needs to drive deep and sustainable development, participate in the prevention and control of the new coronavirus pneumonia epidemic, the recovery and development of the economy, the response to subsequent changes, overcome the phenomenon of depletion of natural resources, and help green transformation and the development of green energy.
Digital transformation needs to participate in the protection and promotion of data bases related to national cultural values, historical traditions, and local customs, and drive digital transformation in the fields of banking, taxation, land management and development, logistics, and others.
The ultimate goal of digital transformation is to make people happier and the country more prosperous and developing.
Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng requires all levels of government, institutions, and enterprises to increase leadership and guidance in the development of digital technology, enhance understanding of digital transformation, continue to develop and improve systems related to digital transformation, strengthen national management, and actively promote the development of digital technology enterprises with a spirit of respect, communication, listening, positivity, and proactivity.
During the forum, Prime Minister Fan Mingzheng attended the award ceremony for the 2021 "Vietnam Made" Outstanding Digital Product Award and the opening ceremony of the "Vietnam Made" Digital Product Exhibition.